name: NutritionFocusedPhysicalFindingsGrouping
title: Nutrition Focused Physical Findings Grouping
purpose: (Clinical Focus: Nutrition related physical appearance, muscle and fat wasting, swallow function, appetite and affect which is used in a comprehensive nutrition focused physical exam for a person.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify characteristics which help define nutritional inadequacies and diagnoses. These elements would be part of "nutrition assessment" data.),(Inclusion Criteria: Clinical terms which describe physical exam findings which relate to nutritional status.),(Exclusion Criteria: Other terms which are considered nutrition assessment data: food/nutrition-related history, anthropometric measurements, biochemical data, medical tests, procedures or client history-are not included in this value set.)

contains.display: Caries of infancy associated with bottle feeding (disorder)
Delay in sexual development AND/OR puberty (disorder)
Pressure injury of sacral region of back (disorder)
Decreased range of cervical spine movement (finding)
Decreased range of thoracic spine movement (finding)
Decreased range of lumbar spine movement (finding)
Finding related to ability to swallow (finding)
Pressure injury of dorsum of foot (disorder)
Pressure injury of coccygeal region of back (disorder)
Atrophy of interosseous muscle of hand (disorder)
Loss of subcutaneous fat overlying rib (finding)
Loss of subcutaneous fat overlying biceps muscle (finding)
Loss of subcutaneous fat overlying triceps muscle (finding)
Abrasions and calluses on knuckles on back of hand due to self-induced vomiting (finding)
